 draft, give you a time to respond etc. &#10;I ask because I thought my son's school were in the process of statementing my son and they wernt! They had arranged for a EP assesment which I assumed was part of the process. &#10;I ended up having to apply myself which was very straightforward.&#10;Things have moved very quickly (although not smoothly) since then.&#10;Is your son on Education Action plus? I think you have to be at this stage before applying but I could be wrong. "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="768" language="en" documentId="4948" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="Becki J" date="31-03-10 21:38" docType="forumpost" origUrl="http://www.netmums.com/coffeehouse/netmums-coffeehouse-archives-528/primary-school-admission-appeals-clinic-599/404307-special-educational-needs-re-mainstream-school-all.html" topic="mainstreaming" thumbsUp="0" thumbsDown="0" origId="4948" notes="" title="Special Educational Needs re. Mainstream school"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="62"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="43" sofa="1" begin="63" end="343"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="47" sofa="1" begin="344" end="521"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="51" sofa="1" begin="522" end="587"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="55" sofa="1" begin="588" end="654"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="59" sofa="1" begin="655" end="768"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39 43 47 51 55 59"/></xmi:XMI>